# UniQuery Backend Validation Test Suite

# Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@studentToken = replace_with_student_jwt_after_login
@facultyToken = replace_with_faculty_jwt_after_login

---
### 3. Authentication Verification
---

# POST /auth/login with correct credentials returns a JWT containing sub, role, institution_id, course_enrollments, jti, exp. [cite: 29]
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "student@example.com",
  "password": "correct_password"
}

###

# Submit 5 wrong passwords for the same account; on 6th attempt assert HTTP 423 with locked_until. [cite: 32]
# Note: Click "Send Request" 6 times to trigger the gate.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "lockout_target@example.com",
  "password": "wrong_password"
}

###

# POST /auth/logout sets revoked_at = now() on the SESSIONS row. [cite: 33] 
# Subsequent requests with that JWT return HTTP 401. [cite: 33]
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}

---
### 4. RBAC Verification
---

# With a STUDENT JWT, POST /api/v1/moderation/decrypt returns HTTP 403. [cite: 35]
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/moderation/decrypt
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "target_id": "encrypted_user_id_string"
}

###

# With a STUDENT JWT, PATCH /api/v1/users/:id returns HTTP 403. [cite: 36]
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/123
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Unauthorized Name Change"
}

###

# With a FACULTY JWT, POST /api/v1/admin/courses/:id/archive returns HTTP 403. [cite: 37]
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/courses/101/archive
Authorization: Bearer {{facultyToken}}

---
### 6. Functional Smoke Tests
---

# POST /api/v1/questions with valid course_id → HTTP 201; question_id returned. [cite: 45]
# Note: Also verifies anonymity engine if you query database afterward. [cite: 26, 45]
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "course_id": "valid_course_id",
  "body": "Is this system truly anonymous?",
  "is_anonymous": true
}

###

# POST /api/v1/questions with invalid course_code → HTTP 422. [cite: 46]
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/questions
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "course_code": "INVALID_CODE",
  "body": "This request should fail validation."
}

###

# POST /api/v1/votes twice with same (voter_id, target_id) → HTTP 409 on second. [cite: 47]
# Note: Click "Send Request" twice.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/votes
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "target_id": "question_123",
  "type": "UPVOTE"
}

###

# POST /api/v1/answers to a LOCKED question → HTTP 423. [cite: 48]
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/answers
Authorization: Bearer {{studentToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question_id": "locked_question_123",
  "body": "Trying to answer a locked thread."
}

###

# PATCH /accept-answer twice on different answers → HTTP 409 on second. [cite: 49]
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/accept-answer
Authorization: Bearer {{facultyToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "answer_id": "answer_123"
}